To check time on all 3 nodes in a single command, you can use oc debug with a loop 👇


---

🔥 Single command (best way)

for node in $(oc get nodes -o name); do echo "===== $node ====="; oc debug $node -- chroot /host date; done


---

✅ Output will look like:

===== node/master1 =====
Fri Apr 10 16:30:00 IST 2026

===== node/master2 =====
Fri Apr 10 16:29:58 IST 2026

===== node/worker1 =====
Fri Apr 10 16:30:02 IST 2026


---

🔍 Alternative (with hostname)

for node in $(oc get nodes -o name); do oc debug $node -- chroot /host sh -c 'echo -n "$(hostname): "; date'; done


---

💡 Pro Tip

If you see time difference > few seconds, it will cause:

TLS errors (like you saw)

MCP issues

etcd instability



